                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/173: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-08T10:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1922—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. Has Department approved terms of loan contract as finally signed by Keith and
                    Keilhauer on June 24th and received here yesterday? It is to be presented to the
                    Congress on Monday for approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
